how to install:
===============

sudo apt-get install emacs-snapshot emacs-extra 
sudo apt-get install ttf-inconsolata 

for the options of emacs-extra I added calculator, Templates and enhanced font lock support

mkdir ~/.emacs.d
cd ~/.emacs.d/

Download emacsonrails:
Users:
git clone git://www.indux.com.ar/emacsonrails.git

Contributors:
git clone git clone git@emacsonrails.org:emacsonrails.git
git submodule init
git submodule update

steps to install:

git submodule init
git submodule update

cd rinari
git submodule init
git submodule update
cd ..

cd org-mode
make
cd ..

cd predictive
make
cd ..

cd gpicker-1.0
sudo apt-get install libgtk2.0-dev libglade2-dev
./configure
make
sudo make install
cd ..

sudo apt-get install ttf-inconsolata

add to your .emacs file
===========
Add to your ~/.emacs file:

; loads emacs on rails
(load "~/.emacs.d/emacsonrails/emacsonrails-loader.el" 'noerror)
(load "~/.emacs.d/emacsonrails/emacsonrails-smart-defaults.el" 'noerror)

Done!


Remote Pair Programming
=======================
We recommend:
Add to ~/.ssh/config

# Where to find the control path, if we have one
Host *
   ControlPath ~/.ssh/master-%r@%h:%p
   ForwardAgent yes
   Compression yes
   ForwardX11 yes

Also, You can replace * with your hostname


How to run emacs multi tty
check: http://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/MultiTTYSupport
1. run emacs on server mode:
    M-x server-start
2. create a window on screen: 
    C-a c
3. Run emacsclient
    emacsclient -c
    -t, --tty               Open a new Emacs frame on the current terminal
    -c, --create-frame      Create a new frame instead of trying to
                        use the current Emacs frame

emacs-snapshot repo
===================
add to /etc/apt/sources.list

# emacs
deb http://ppa.launchpad.net/ubuntu-elisp/ubuntu/ intrepid main
deb-src http://ppa.launchpad.net/ubuntu-elisp/ubuntu/ intrepid main
